node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Teacher Misery on September 09, 2021 tagging @beautandbeastco. May be an image of text that says '北 beautandbeastco Today a student knocked over over trash cans, my things, punched me in the face, bit me, and slapped me multiple times.'.

node.text: This is everything. It's not about how the student acted (though that sounds very difficult to handle), it's about how the adults responded. It's about support versus neglect or worse... BLAME. (I've been asked, after a student called me a bitch on the very first day of class, what I did to provoke this response. I was simply introducing myself. "Well, perhaps there was something about you or your classroom that made the student feel unwelcome. We're going to start observing you to see how you can work on developing better relationships with your students.") Can you fucking imagine??? 🖕🖕🖕🖕
